1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:40,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:49,404 --> 00:00:52,073
STILL SHINING

3
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:54,826
Tae-seo.

4
00:01:03,793 --> 00:01:05,336
The people you long to see

5
00:01:06,004 --> 00:01:07,422
never appear in your dreams.

6
00:01:11,342 --> 00:01:12,552
Tae-seo.

7
00:01:21,227 --> 00:01:22,228
So…

8
00:01:22,979 --> 00:01:24,147
this isn't a dream.

9
00:01:26,191 --> 00:01:27,233
She'd never appear in one.

10
00:02:18,243 --> 00:02:19,577
You're up.

11
00:02:22,121 --> 00:02:24,332
I found a place that was open
this early in the morning.

12
00:02:25,959 --> 00:02:27,669
These were leftovers from yesterday.

13
00:02:27,752 --> 00:02:29,170
The mushy ones were even cheaper.

14
00:02:29,254 --> 00:02:30,797
You should blend these.

15
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:32,298
Wait, you don't have a blender.

16
00:02:32,382 --> 00:02:33,841
You should cut out the bad bits.

17
00:02:33,925 --> 00:02:35,885
You didn't have food waste bags either.

18
00:02:35,969 --> 00:02:37,303
You should buy some…

19
00:02:41,599 --> 00:02:42,934
Stop staring.

20
00:03:27,562 --> 00:03:28,771
Want some grapes?

21
00:03:29,605 --> 00:03:31,524
I washed the ones that were still decent.

22
00:03:38,031 --> 00:03:38,865
Have one.

23
00:03:40,074 --> 00:03:41,534
It must be sour after brushing.

24
00:03:44,078 --> 00:03:44,912
It's good.

25
00:03:54,088 --> 00:03:55,465
Why didn't you wake me up?

26
00:03:57,967 --> 00:03:59,260
When do you get off work?

27
00:03:59,344 --> 00:04:01,721
At 6:00 p.m. You should've woken me up.

28
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:04,349
We could've stayed up all night together.

29
00:04:06,351 --> 00:04:08,061
From now on, I'm going to be in Seoul

30
00:04:08,895 --> 00:04:11,230
managing an old guesthouse,

31
00:04:11,314 --> 00:04:13,441
so we can meet up for a bit after work.

32
00:04:14,984 --> 00:04:16,361
We live close by now.

33
00:04:22,617 --> 00:04:23,701
Take care.

34
00:04:36,422 --> 00:04:38,216
-Bye.
-Okay, bye.

35
00:05:23,261 --> 00:05:30,226
STILL SHINING

36
00:05:35,690 --> 00:05:37,066
Due to the morning commute,

37
00:05:37,150 --> 00:05:38,818
the train is very crowded.

38
00:05:38,901 --> 00:05:40,361
Please be considerate of others.

39
00:05:41,654 --> 00:05:44,031
We hope that somewhere today, joy…

40
00:05:47,285 --> 00:05:50,913
something that brings you joy awaits you.

41
00:05:50,997 --> 00:05:52,331
Thank you.

42
00:05:56,878 --> 00:05:59,839
Hey, look at the compliments
coming in about Yeon Tae-seo.

43
00:05:59,922 --> 00:06:02,258
Five, six.

44
00:06:02,341 --> 00:06:03,801
What did he say?

45
00:06:03,885 --> 00:06:07,138
"I hope something
that brings you joy awaits you."

46
00:06:07,221 --> 00:06:08,681
I like that! Right?

47
00:06:08,764 --> 00:06:11,559
He only ever says the train is
"Coming to a stop" or "Departing."

48
00:06:12,059 --> 00:06:13,769
-Hey!
-Yes?

49
00:06:13,853 --> 00:06:15,062
What did you say today?

50
00:06:16,856 --> 00:06:19,859
Nothing much. Have a good one.

51
00:06:19,942 --> 00:06:21,402
I hope you find joy too.

52
00:06:21,485 --> 00:06:22,945
Right, you too.

53
00:07:00,691 --> 00:07:01,609
Tae-seo.

54
00:07:16,499 --> 00:07:17,458
Shall we go?

55
00:07:28,553 --> 00:07:31,138
I heard this is a famous photo spot.

56
00:07:47,154 --> 00:07:48,155
Yeon Namsan.

57
00:07:51,075 --> 00:07:54,370
It's okay for you to face me now.

58
00:07:58,666 --> 00:07:59,667
This can't be real.

59
00:08:01,252 --> 00:08:03,212
It feels like a dream.

60
00:08:09,594 --> 00:08:13,139
Do you want to walk a bit further?
Or want to take more photos here?

61
00:08:14,557 --> 00:08:15,808
Let's go a bit further.

62
00:08:39,624 --> 00:08:42,627
I dropped by a photo store on my way home
and had it developed.

63
00:08:44,462 --> 00:08:46,339
Good night, Tae-seo.

64
00:08:52,595 --> 00:08:55,890
I'll put these in the wash
at the laundromat on my way home.

65
00:08:57,016 --> 00:08:59,977
Please put them in the dryer later,
and then bring them back here.

66
00:09:00,061 --> 00:09:03,105
You'll have to make two trips.

67
00:09:03,189 --> 00:09:05,107
I didn't hear anything about a laundromat.

68
00:09:05,191 --> 00:09:07,860
I was told a professional laundry service

69
00:09:07,943 --> 00:09:10,237
picks them up and brings them back.

70
00:09:10,321 --> 00:09:11,197
They used to.

71
00:09:13,949 --> 00:09:15,576
They quit a month ago.

72
00:09:15,660 --> 00:09:19,163
The boss said he'd look for another one,
but who knows if he is.

73
00:09:40,601 --> 00:09:42,603
I should eat a hearty meal
and keep my energy up.

74
00:09:59,620 --> 00:10:03,499
PAYMENT COMPLETE

75
00:10:12,425 --> 00:10:14,093
I'll come see you at work.

76
00:10:18,055 --> 00:10:19,348
At work…

77
00:10:23,394 --> 00:10:26,772
If I stop by Unit 203 after work,
it'll be around the time you get off.

78
00:10:27,273 --> 00:10:28,566
I'll come to you.

79
00:10:29,650 --> 00:10:31,569
I want to spend a day in your shoes.

80
00:10:32,111 --> 00:10:33,988
All the things you see every day in Seoul,

81
00:10:34,572 --> 00:10:35,406
I want to see too.

82
00:10:35,489 --> 00:10:39,076
DONGJAK STATION EXIT 2

83
00:10:51,422 --> 00:10:52,423
Mo Eun-a.

84
00:11:05,519 --> 00:11:07,229
-Can I ask something?
-Sure.

85
00:11:07,980 --> 00:11:09,857
Will you be staying in Unit 203?

86
00:11:10,900 --> 00:11:12,109
Just for the time being.

87
00:11:12,651 --> 00:11:15,112
They felt bad and let me
have the house for two weeks.

88
00:11:16,155 --> 00:11:17,448
And I found a place to live.

89
00:11:17,531 --> 00:11:20,409
It's where the previous manager lived.
The dates work out perfectly.

90
00:11:20,493 --> 00:11:21,744
The Monday after next.

91
00:11:22,411 --> 00:11:24,205
Are you free then? Anytime in the evening?

92
00:11:25,039 --> 00:11:26,415
Hold on, I'll check.

93
00:11:26,499 --> 00:11:28,834
I'm going to have a small party that day.

94
00:11:28,918 --> 00:11:31,337
My roommate, you, and me.

95
00:11:31,420 --> 00:11:33,172
The three of us. Nothing fancy.

96
00:11:33,881 --> 00:11:35,299
The start of my life in Seoul.

97
00:11:39,011 --> 00:11:40,179
I can make it.

98
00:11:43,474 --> 00:11:45,226
It won't be easy
to follow my daily routine.

99
00:11:48,187 --> 00:11:49,522
-What are you doing?
-What?

100
00:11:50,147 --> 00:11:51,398
Do I need a full warm-up?

101
00:11:51,482 --> 00:11:54,151
No, we're going to run.
Why are you only warming up your hands?

102
00:11:55,069 --> 00:11:56,570
Come on, do your legs too.

103
00:11:58,322 --> 00:11:59,698
One, two.

104
00:12:01,659 --> 00:12:03,244
Three, four.

105
00:12:04,203 --> 00:12:05,037
The other side.

106
00:12:12,294 --> 00:12:13,212
I'm exhausted.

107
00:12:14,255 --> 00:12:15,464
Let's take a break.

108
00:12:17,174 --> 00:12:18,259
Are you okay?

109
00:12:23,931 --> 00:12:26,475
So you see this every day
on your way home.

110
00:12:27,351 --> 00:12:29,478
You'd have a great view
of the fireworks festival.

111
00:12:29,562 --> 00:12:32,273
I was always so jealous
when Seoul would hold fireworks festivals.

112
00:12:32,356 --> 00:12:33,607
It's right there.

113
00:12:36,652 --> 00:12:37,653
That way.

114
00:12:37,736 --> 00:12:38,862
It's that way.

115
00:12:40,155 --> 00:12:41,740
So that's Yeouido.

116
00:12:43,826 --> 00:12:45,744
Where's your energy?

117
00:12:50,124 --> 00:12:51,083
So…

118
00:12:52,543 --> 00:12:54,587
I don't know many restaurants

119
00:12:54,670 --> 00:12:56,547
or any good food spots,

120
00:12:56,630 --> 00:12:58,299
but this one's the best place I've tried,

121
00:12:59,008 --> 00:13:00,593
and the food's high in protein.

122
00:13:01,677 --> 00:13:04,054
There's one thing
I'm worried about though.

123
00:13:06,807 --> 00:13:08,017
He's here.

124
00:13:15,524 --> 00:13:18,235
You're both acting so shocked.

125
00:13:18,319 --> 00:13:19,945
How could I not be shocked by this?

126
00:13:21,447 --> 00:13:23,741
I've never seen Yeon Tae-seo
hang out with anyone else.

127
00:13:23,824 --> 00:13:24,742
Right.

128
00:13:24,825 --> 00:13:28,162
Yeon Tae-seo's always alone.
He'd always been studying by himself.

129
00:13:28,245 --> 00:13:29,496
He has no friends.

130
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:33,000
Geez, were you like that over there too?
Boring, like eating rice with no meat?

131
00:13:34,126 --> 00:13:35,461
Ma'am!

132
00:13:36,295 --> 00:13:37,630
-Soju?
-You bet.

133
00:13:38,130 --> 00:13:40,090
-Ma'am, I'm taking a bottle of soju!
-Okay.

134
00:13:43,260 --> 00:13:45,137
Did Tae-seo ever mention me?

135
00:13:45,220 --> 00:13:46,847
-Your name is…
-Mo Eun-a.

136
00:13:46,930 --> 00:13:48,891
He bad-mouthed me, right? What did he say?

137
00:13:48,974 --> 00:13:51,560
Come on, why does that matter?
The present is what counts.

138
00:13:52,186 --> 00:13:53,187
You don't know who I am.

139
00:13:53,812 --> 00:13:55,397
Right, today's the first time…

140
00:13:57,191 --> 00:13:58,317
Actually, no!

141
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,943
You must be that…

142
00:14:00,027 --> 00:14:01,487
By any chance, how old…

143
00:14:04,782 --> 00:14:05,699
Never mind.

144
00:14:05,783 --> 00:14:08,035
What? Tell me! Who is he talking about?

145
00:14:08,994 --> 00:14:10,371
-No clue.
-That older girl.

146
00:14:10,454 --> 00:14:11,830
Just drink.

147
00:14:12,414 --> 00:14:15,459
Geez, how did that older girl
end up being forgotten like that?

148
00:14:16,710 --> 00:14:18,253
Hey, Yeon Tae-seo.

149
00:14:19,004 --> 00:14:20,047
We only dated briefly.

150
00:14:20,130 --> 00:14:22,591
She was crazy about him. I even cried.

151
00:14:23,258 --> 00:14:24,343
Now, I'm curious.

152
00:14:24,426 --> 00:14:25,719
What did she do?

153
00:14:29,640 --> 00:14:31,016
She was very pure.

154
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:32,267
Stop making things up.

155
00:14:32,351 --> 00:14:34,937
She was purely persistent.

156
00:14:35,020 --> 00:14:38,023
-And also, when was that again?
-"Also"?

157
00:14:38,107 --> 00:14:39,775
-Perhaps…
-Nothing.

158
00:14:39,858 --> 00:14:42,069
Right, there's nothing in my glass.

159
00:14:44,780 --> 00:14:46,198
It looks like you can really drink.

160
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:48,826
Only take a glass or two.

161
00:14:49,451 --> 00:14:50,744
I can't drink more than that.

162
00:14:51,996 --> 00:14:53,998
I'd only drink just one glass
with the guests too.

163
00:14:54,081 --> 00:14:54,915
Guests?

164
00:14:56,208 --> 00:14:57,626
I used to run a guesthouse.

165
00:14:58,335 --> 00:15:00,254
I poured my heart and soul into it,

166
00:15:00,879 --> 00:15:02,214
but I got blindsided.

167
00:15:02,715 --> 00:15:03,924
They took everything.

168
00:15:04,925 --> 00:15:06,677
Man, that must've been hard. Cheers!

169
00:15:07,469 --> 00:15:08,846
I got way too serious.

170
00:15:08,929 --> 00:15:09,763
I'll stop here.

171
00:15:09,847 --> 00:15:11,265
Yeah, we only just met.

172
00:15:11,348 --> 00:15:13,058
I was a little thrown off.

173
00:15:13,142 --> 00:15:14,184
Sorry.

174
00:15:15,185 --> 00:15:17,312
A lot of girls liked Tae-seo
in high school, right?

175
00:15:17,396 --> 00:15:20,024
-Nope. We went to an all-boys school.
-Yeah, it was all boys.

176
00:15:20,107 --> 00:15:21,150
What?

177
00:15:21,233 --> 00:15:24,611
But when he first transferred,
his bag was full of girls' name tags.

178
00:15:24,695 --> 00:15:26,155
What? It was only one or two.

179
00:15:27,364 --> 00:15:28,699
It must be from the study center.

180
00:15:29,867 --> 00:15:31,577
You did something behind my back!

181
00:15:32,202 --> 00:15:33,954
Hey, who did you get name tags from?

182
00:15:34,038 --> 00:15:36,248
I told you it's rude to point like that.

183
00:15:36,331 --> 00:15:37,624
Who was it?

184
00:15:40,252 --> 00:15:41,336
Hey.

185
00:15:41,420 --> 00:15:43,672
I saw that. Ma'am!

186
00:15:43,756 --> 00:15:45,299
You don't allow takeout here.

187
00:15:45,382 --> 00:15:47,593
Why does A-sol's family
always get special treatment?

188
00:15:47,676 --> 00:15:48,719
Just let it go.

189
00:16:09,656 --> 00:16:12,534
Are you okay? You were drinking a lot.

190
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:16,080
Yeah, I'm pleasantly tipsy.

191
00:16:18,332 --> 00:16:20,417
So you were here
before you came to Yeonwoo.

192
00:16:24,505 --> 00:16:25,339
Earlier…

193
00:16:28,342 --> 00:16:30,052
what did you mean by "blindsided"?

194
00:16:31,637 --> 00:16:33,555
I was living in the residence hall,

195
00:16:33,639 --> 00:16:37,351
and then I thought I'd try living
in a proper house for once.

196
00:16:38,852 --> 00:16:42,397
But I didn't rewrite the contract
when I turned it into a guesthouse.

197
00:16:42,940 --> 00:16:44,358
They said it was fine.

198
00:16:47,027 --> 00:16:49,113
But when I started doing well,
they kicked me out.

199
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:53,909
Then, I came to Seoul

200
00:16:54,952 --> 00:16:56,745
and met Yeon Tae-seo.

201
00:17:03,377 --> 00:17:05,671
How long did you go out
with that older girl?

202
00:17:09,258 --> 00:17:10,217
A year.

203
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:16,014
A year is quite a long while
for Yeon Tae-seo.

204
00:17:16,598 --> 00:17:18,142
That's how long I've known her for.

205
00:17:18,892 --> 00:17:20,060
I dated her for…

206
00:17:21,311 --> 00:17:22,896
less than a month, I think.

207
00:17:23,647 --> 00:17:24,565
You?

208
00:17:26,150 --> 00:17:27,860
That person you're ending things with.

209
00:17:28,610 --> 00:17:30,279
How long did you two date?

210
00:17:32,531 --> 00:17:33,699
About three months.

211
00:17:34,491 --> 00:17:35,909
I've known him for longer.

212
00:17:42,416 --> 00:17:43,876
Your profile hasn't changed.

213
00:17:47,254 --> 00:17:49,339
We usually sat next to each other.

214
00:17:50,382 --> 00:17:53,677
In the library and on bus trips.

215
00:17:54,928 --> 00:17:58,098
It's strange, but when I think of you,
I think of your profile.

216
00:18:01,935 --> 00:18:03,187
But something's different.

217
00:18:04,229 --> 00:18:05,898
Maybe it's the air around you?

218
00:18:07,399 --> 00:18:08,692
You're exactly the same.

219
00:18:08,775 --> 00:18:10,611
I looked like this when I was 20?

220
00:18:11,195 --> 00:18:12,654
No way.

221
00:18:14,198 --> 00:18:15,657
There's something that's different.

222
00:18:16,325 --> 00:18:17,159
You…

223
00:18:17,868 --> 00:18:20,537
do these gestures when you're talking now.

224
00:18:22,289 --> 00:18:23,790
What is this?

225
00:18:23,874 --> 00:18:25,626
Did I not do that before?

226
00:18:26,376 --> 00:18:27,336
You too, actually.

227
00:18:27,419 --> 00:18:30,047
It was when you casually said earlier,

228
00:18:30,130 --> 00:18:31,256
"A year."

229
00:18:32,549 --> 00:18:34,301
That didn't feel like you.

230
00:18:36,595 --> 00:18:39,306
But then again, maybe it is like you.

231
00:18:41,266 --> 00:18:42,601
You and I both…

232
00:18:43,936 --> 00:18:44,770
Well,

233
00:18:45,437 --> 00:18:48,523
it's our first time seeing someone
we broke up with after ten years.

234
00:18:58,367 --> 00:18:59,993
We didn't break up.

235
00:19:04,164 --> 00:19:05,332
It didn't happen in person.

236
00:19:05,999 --> 00:19:08,085
How can we break up
without even seeing each other?

237
00:19:08,168 --> 00:19:10,170
-Hey…
-That's what I kept telling myself.

238
00:19:12,214 --> 00:19:13,924
Then, I eventually accepted it.

239
00:19:15,342 --> 00:19:17,010
"We didn't break up."

240
00:19:17,678 --> 00:19:20,138
"I can't break up with Tae-seo like this."

241
00:19:22,516 --> 00:19:25,018
We ended things in July, so…

242
00:19:30,565 --> 00:19:32,276
I told myself that for six months.

243
00:19:33,277 --> 00:19:34,111
Then…

244
00:19:36,029 --> 00:19:37,030
Then?

245
00:19:38,657 --> 00:19:40,450
Then, I stopped convincing myself.

246
00:19:42,536 --> 00:19:45,080
What about you?
You didn't think of it that way at all?

247
00:19:46,456 --> 00:19:47,874
When it's over, it's over.

248
00:19:49,793 --> 00:19:53,839
I didn't think
there would be anything more.

249
00:19:57,301 --> 00:19:58,427
It's over.

250
00:19:59,386 --> 00:20:01,388
What we had then is over.

251
00:20:02,222 --> 00:20:03,432
Now…

252
00:20:04,725 --> 00:20:05,934
we're different,

253
00:20:07,019 --> 00:20:07,936
but also the same…

254
00:20:09,730 --> 00:20:10,856
No.

255
00:20:12,024 --> 00:20:12,858
Never mind.

256
00:20:19,698 --> 00:20:21,199
I'm surprised by that too.

257
00:20:26,872 --> 00:20:28,040
It's the same.

258
00:20:29,374 --> 00:20:31,043
My feelings are the same.

259
00:20:33,128 --> 00:20:35,339
You're someone I liked ten years ago,

260
00:20:37,132 --> 00:20:38,675
but I still feel the same way.

261
00:20:40,969 --> 00:20:43,221
I didn't know that would be possible,

262
00:20:46,016 --> 00:20:47,351
but it's been seamless.

263
00:20:49,728 --> 00:20:50,562
Me too.

264
00:20:52,981 --> 00:20:55,359
It was like that the moment I saw you.

265
00:21:03,158 --> 00:21:05,494
I guess no one can defeat
Mo Eun-a from ten years ago…

266
00:21:09,164 --> 00:21:11,083
except Mo Eun-a herself.

267
00:21:16,171 --> 00:21:17,005
That's really nice.

268
00:21:18,298 --> 00:21:20,467
It feels like
everything's been made up for.

269
00:21:22,094 --> 00:21:23,136
Then…

270
00:21:27,265 --> 00:21:29,017
we're back together again?

271
00:21:41,113 --> 00:21:42,697
Thanks, Tae-seo.

272
00:21:46,952 --> 00:21:49,121
Why would they fight in a study café?

273
00:21:49,204 --> 00:21:51,373
Geez, kids are scary these days.

274
00:21:54,084 --> 00:21:56,545
You can sit down. It's okay to ignore him.

275
00:21:56,628 --> 00:21:57,587
Okay.

276
00:22:03,677 --> 00:22:05,887
She's that girl from ten years ago, right?

277
00:22:08,557 --> 00:22:12,811
I pretended not to know on purpose
and even talked about that older girl.

278
00:22:12,894 --> 00:22:15,605
I made it sound like
you did just fine without her.

279
00:22:18,442 --> 00:22:19,526
Give me one too.

280
00:22:20,110 --> 00:22:22,195
-You don't smoke.
-Just give me one.

281
00:23:32,807 --> 00:23:35,101
-Did you sleep well?
-Yes, we did.

282
00:23:36,061 --> 00:23:39,439
I thought this might help you find
some nice places to visit around here.

283
00:23:39,522 --> 00:23:41,399
Yes, thank you. We'll take a look.

284
00:23:47,781 --> 00:23:50,617
Tell me what needs to stay
or be thrown away.

285
00:23:50,700 --> 00:23:52,661
I'm cleaning out the back house.

286
00:24:08,885 --> 00:24:10,512
You don't need to clean it out.

287
00:24:13,139 --> 00:24:16,977
You want me to leave your things to rot?
Just tell me what you'll keep.

288
00:24:17,060 --> 00:24:20,272
Send all the clothes and bedding
to the community center.

289
00:24:20,355 --> 00:24:21,856
They'll sort it out themselves.

290
00:24:22,565 --> 00:24:24,276
Just send the items
I've listed to Yeonwoo.

291
00:24:24,859 --> 00:24:26,736
You're not even going to Yeonwoo.

292
00:24:26,820 --> 00:24:29,072
Send me your address in Seoul
that I can send these to.

293
00:24:35,829 --> 00:24:37,831
I'll come see you after I finish work.

294
00:24:37,914 --> 00:24:40,417
Tell me your nearest station.
I'll go only as far as there.

295
00:24:55,557 --> 00:24:56,808
Hello.

296
00:24:58,518 --> 00:24:59,978
I'm Train Operator Choi Su-cheol.

297
00:25:00,562 --> 00:25:02,897
-I took photos of Oido Station.
-Right.

298
00:25:02,981 --> 00:25:04,316
-Hello.
-Hello.

299
00:25:04,399 --> 00:25:06,234
I believe we've only spoken over texts

300
00:25:06,318 --> 00:25:08,903
since train operators
rarely get to see each other.

301
00:25:08,987 --> 00:25:11,406
Did you hear
about the frame size and wood type?

302
00:25:11,489 --> 00:25:13,658
I did, but actually…

303
00:25:14,326 --> 00:25:16,286
I'd like to change the photo.

304
00:25:17,412 --> 00:25:18,788
Could you take a look?

305
00:25:18,872 --> 00:25:20,081
-Do you have it with you?
-Yes.

306
00:25:20,790 --> 00:25:22,834
Some had been taken before,

307
00:25:22,917 --> 00:25:23,960
and a few were retaken.

308
00:25:24,711 --> 00:25:27,213
-They're really good.
-Thank you.

309
00:25:27,922 --> 00:25:30,091
-Sorry, one second.
-Sure.

310
00:25:32,427 --> 00:25:34,763
I have to stay here this evening.

311
00:25:34,846 --> 00:25:37,515
I'm meeting my boss for the first time
since coming to Seoul.

312
00:25:37,599 --> 00:25:40,393
I think he has something to say to me.
Let's meet another day.

313
00:25:41,895 --> 00:25:43,188
Those flowers…

314
00:25:44,147 --> 00:25:45,398
Don't put them in the rooms.

315
00:25:45,482 --> 00:25:47,942
If we stop doing that later,
people will complain.

316
00:25:48,026 --> 00:25:48,943
And in the break room,

317
00:25:49,027 --> 00:25:51,321
do not use the gas
under any circumstances.

318
00:25:52,697 --> 00:25:55,658
There was a manager
who once secretly ate and slept there,

319
00:25:55,742 --> 00:25:57,410
and then a fire broke out one night.

320
00:25:57,494 --> 00:25:58,328
Okay.

321
00:25:59,537 --> 00:26:00,997
What about the laundry service?

322
00:26:01,623 --> 00:26:03,541
I'm trying to find one.

323
00:26:03,625 --> 00:26:05,794
But maybe I'll make a laundry room.
What do you think?

324
00:26:06,669 --> 00:26:09,464
A professional service is much better.
They use different equipment.

325
00:26:09,547 --> 00:26:11,591
Washing machines
are really good these days.

326
00:26:14,219 --> 00:26:16,805
By the way, when Hae-jin
handed over duties to you,

327
00:26:17,597 --> 00:26:20,308
she didn't mention that
we don't have reservations from next week.

328
00:26:20,392 --> 00:26:22,310
It's being rented out for two weeks.

329
00:26:22,394 --> 00:26:24,562
They'll be filming here,
so it won't be busy.

330
00:26:24,646 --> 00:26:26,398
You can just stay here
until you clock out.

331
00:26:45,875 --> 00:26:46,751
SEONG-CHAN

332
00:26:46,835 --> 00:26:49,337
YOU'RE NOT EVEN GOING TO YEONWOO

333
00:26:49,421 --> 00:26:52,882
SEND ME YOUR ADDRESS IN SEOUL
THAT I CAN SEND THESE TO

334
00:26:55,260 --> 00:26:57,220
Just leave my things to rot
in the back house.

335
00:27:08,773 --> 00:27:09,941
Someone's exhausted.

336
00:27:18,032 --> 00:27:18,867
Eun-a.

337
00:27:20,743 --> 00:27:22,036
No, I just…

338
00:27:22,745 --> 00:27:23,913
Sorry.

339
00:27:24,497 --> 00:27:25,707
It's just that…

340
00:27:26,541 --> 00:27:27,500
Somehow,

341
00:27:28,626 --> 00:27:30,962
when I was feeling exhausted after work,

342
00:27:31,963 --> 00:27:34,340
you're standing here right in front of me.

343
00:27:35,258 --> 00:27:37,093
The very person I wanted to see.

344
00:27:38,386 --> 00:27:39,220
How?

345
00:27:39,304 --> 00:27:41,097
You should've said you wanted to see me.

346
00:27:45,643 --> 00:27:46,769
Well…

347
00:27:46,853 --> 00:27:49,689
It's not that hard.
I can be here in no time.

348
00:27:57,989 --> 00:27:59,282
You made it through well today

349
00:28:00,575 --> 00:28:01,576
in this tough city.

350
00:28:16,132 --> 00:28:18,468
I need Yeon Tae-seo's broad back.

351
00:28:20,261 --> 00:28:21,846
Not my arms but my back?

352
00:28:27,268 --> 00:28:28,645
I need your back for today.

353
00:28:31,689 --> 00:28:33,107
This feels nice.

354
00:29:04,097 --> 00:29:07,767
Let's meet at my workplace today.
I'll send you the address.

355
00:29:19,904 --> 00:29:21,281
You're really good at your job.

356
00:29:34,252 --> 00:29:35,628
What is it?

357
00:29:35,712 --> 00:29:37,589
The lamp's broken, so I'm checking it.

358
00:29:37,672 --> 00:29:39,591
-Just wait one second.
-Okay.

359
00:30:19,130 --> 00:30:20,465
Nice.

360
00:30:26,095 --> 00:30:27,472
Thanks for the ice cream.

361
00:30:28,890 --> 00:30:29,933
Hey.

362
00:30:59,629 --> 00:31:00,755
I need some coffee.

363
00:31:15,019 --> 00:31:15,853
Say "Ah."

364
00:31:17,105 --> 00:31:19,273
Eat this. They say it helps you wake up.

365
00:31:23,361 --> 00:31:25,697
Thanks. You're helping me focus.

366
00:31:33,121 --> 00:31:34,747
Why does he want to change the photo?

367
00:31:35,498 --> 00:31:36,582
Well…

368
00:31:37,250 --> 00:31:39,419
Now that the exhibition
is really happening,

369
00:31:39,502 --> 00:31:40,503
I guess he's unsure.

370
00:31:41,170 --> 00:31:42,463
He even brought his old photos.

371
00:31:43,923 --> 00:31:45,341
But I like that one.

372
00:31:47,719 --> 00:31:48,553
Me too.

373
00:31:49,429 --> 00:31:51,431
He said he'll think about it some more.

374
00:31:53,016 --> 00:31:55,184
Is there anything I can do?
I want to help.

375
00:31:58,855 --> 00:32:00,064
Should I clean up?

376
00:32:00,148 --> 00:32:01,107
No, it's okay.

377
00:32:03,776 --> 00:32:06,029
Put these photos on the board for me.

378
00:32:07,071 --> 00:32:08,865
-Any way I want to?
-Sure.

379
00:32:38,311 --> 00:32:39,979
Are these scraps? Can I use them?

380
00:32:40,855 --> 00:32:41,898
Sure.

381
00:32:55,620 --> 00:32:57,205
Are you going to keep living in Seoul?

382
00:33:01,250 --> 00:33:02,627
That might be difficult.

383
00:33:02,710 --> 00:33:04,837
Hui-seo's just bought me some time.

384
00:33:05,505 --> 00:33:08,216
When my grandparents become
too much for him, I need to move back.

385
00:33:11,636 --> 00:33:14,514
Was that your plan from the start?

386
00:33:15,473 --> 00:33:16,307
Yeah.

387
00:33:17,767 --> 00:33:19,435
Just for a brief while,

388
00:33:20,186 --> 00:33:23,314
I thought I could put myself first.

389
00:33:26,275 --> 00:33:27,860
My life here

390
00:33:29,362 --> 00:33:30,530
has an expiration date.

391
00:33:31,989 --> 00:33:33,741
Hui-seo might be able to handle it.

392
00:33:34,784 --> 00:33:35,743
It'll be hard.

393
00:33:37,537 --> 00:33:39,831
He still can't travel outside Yeonwoo.

394
00:33:40,456 --> 00:33:43,084
He's made a life for himself in that town,

395
00:33:43,793 --> 00:33:44,961
and I'm proud of him.

396
00:33:46,504 --> 00:33:47,964
I can't wish for more.

397
00:33:57,682 --> 00:33:58,891
Until when?

398
00:34:05,231 --> 00:34:06,524
Why aren't you answering?

399
00:34:11,696 --> 00:34:14,365
You asked, so I thought about it.

400
00:34:14,448 --> 00:34:15,283
But…

401
00:34:16,409 --> 00:34:18,995
I don't really know if that's up to me.

402
00:34:19,662 --> 00:34:22,915
It could be sooner than expected
or much later.

403
00:34:25,668 --> 00:34:27,211
I'll think about it when I get there.

404
00:34:28,588 --> 00:34:31,299
Will you be able to settle things quickly
when the time comes?

405
00:34:32,717 --> 00:34:33,759
I have to.

406
00:34:38,931 --> 00:34:40,516
I hope it goes the way you want.

407
00:34:44,478 --> 00:34:45,521
Do you…

408
00:34:46,606 --> 00:34:48,232
see yourself getting married?

409
00:34:53,571 --> 00:34:54,405
Yeah.

410
00:34:58,951 --> 00:34:59,785
What about you?

411
00:35:01,996 --> 00:35:04,582
I've never even dared to think about it.

412
00:35:06,334 --> 00:35:09,337
You're going to live
in either Seoul or Yeonwoo, right?

413
00:35:12,256 --> 00:35:13,382
I'll have to see.

414
00:35:14,133 --> 00:35:16,093
Deciding where to live

415
00:35:16,177 --> 00:35:17,762
isn't as easy as it seems.

416
00:35:19,263 --> 00:35:20,431
Still,

417
00:35:20,514 --> 00:35:22,767
wherever it is,
I feel comfortable when I'm with you.

418
00:35:24,977 --> 00:35:28,105
When you're traveling,
that place feels like reality,

419
00:35:28,814 --> 00:35:30,316
and your actual home feels distant.

420
00:35:30,983 --> 00:35:32,485
But when you come back,

421
00:35:32,568 --> 00:35:34,654
your home feels real,

422
00:35:34,737 --> 00:35:36,072
and where you were feels distant,

423
00:35:37,031 --> 00:35:38,241
as if it was fake.

424
00:35:41,202 --> 00:35:43,496
It felt unreal being in Seoul.

425
00:35:44,247 --> 00:35:46,374
I ended up coming here out of nowhere.

426
00:35:49,293 --> 00:35:51,045
I told myself this wasn't real

427
00:35:51,754 --> 00:35:53,422
and I was trapped inside a lie.

428
00:35:54,298 --> 00:35:58,135
But when I look at you,
this place feels real.

429
00:36:00,096 --> 00:36:01,555
I think, "That's right."

430
00:36:01,639 --> 00:36:02,640
"It was here."

431
00:36:05,768 --> 00:36:06,769
You were here,

432
00:36:06,852 --> 00:36:08,354
so it became real.

433
00:36:10,231 --> 00:36:11,941
You said the same thing back then.

434
00:36:12,775 --> 00:36:14,360
You remember that?

435
00:36:15,820 --> 00:36:17,196
So…

436
00:36:21,325 --> 00:36:22,660
stay right by my side.

437
00:36:23,911 --> 00:36:25,496
Okay, I will.

438
00:36:30,459 --> 00:36:32,628
When was your loneliest birthday?

439
00:36:33,879 --> 00:36:35,131
Where did that come from?

440
00:36:36,590 --> 00:36:38,259
We've never celebrated our birthdays.

441
00:36:38,342 --> 00:36:40,344
Mine's July 28th,

442
00:36:40,428 --> 00:36:41,721
the day before you transferred.

443
00:36:41,804 --> 00:36:43,514
Yours is November 9th.

444
00:36:44,223 --> 00:36:46,475
But you never told me,
so we just spent it studying.

445
00:36:46,976 --> 00:36:49,020
Tell me. I just need to write the date.

446
00:36:49,103 --> 00:36:50,479
When was your loneliest birthday?

447
00:36:53,858 --> 00:36:55,776
It was in 2016 when I was in the army.

448
00:37:00,698 --> 00:37:02,283
Besides 2016.

449
00:37:03,993 --> 00:37:06,162
Last year? I'll pick last year.

450
00:37:07,496 --> 00:37:09,290
Were you lonely last year?

451
00:37:09,373 --> 00:37:11,834
You told me to think about it,
so I did just that.

452
00:37:11,917 --> 00:37:13,252
It doesn't mean anything.

453
00:37:25,598 --> 00:37:26,682
Ta-da!

454
00:37:27,641 --> 00:37:29,852
Congratulations on the last birthday
of your twenties.

455
00:37:33,856 --> 00:37:37,026
HAPPY BIRTHDAY
NOVEMBER 9, 2024

456
00:37:45,409 --> 00:37:46,452
And my present?

457
00:37:47,828 --> 00:37:48,704
Your present?

458
00:37:51,040 --> 00:37:51,874
Your present…

459
00:37:59,006 --> 00:37:59,840
Happy birthday.

460
00:38:03,469 --> 00:38:04,595
Happy?

461
00:38:14,230 --> 00:38:15,523
Hui-seo's calling.

462
00:38:16,107 --> 00:38:17,358
It must be urgent.

463
00:38:17,983 --> 00:38:18,943
You should pick up.

464
00:38:19,443 --> 00:38:20,361
One second.

465
00:38:21,987 --> 00:38:22,822
Hey, Hui-seo.

466
00:38:22,905 --> 00:38:25,074
You know Grandma's going
to the hospital next week?

467
00:38:25,658 --> 00:38:27,535
I know. She's getting a checkup.

468
00:38:28,744 --> 00:38:31,497
I'm going to take her,
so I just called to tell you not to worry.

469
00:38:33,207 --> 00:38:34,667
Weren't you worried?

470
00:38:34,750 --> 00:38:37,920
Why would I be? You'll do just fine.

471
00:38:38,003 --> 00:38:40,381
Anyway, just give Grandma a call.

472
00:38:40,464 --> 00:38:43,134
Do I really have to remind you
to call her though?

473
00:38:43,217 --> 00:38:44,677
You could at least say,

474
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:48,097
"I should be there, but I can't go.
Man, I feel terrible."

475
00:38:48,180 --> 00:38:49,765
Is that so hard?

476
00:38:49,849 --> 00:38:51,517
Don't you even feel sorry for me?

477
00:38:51,600 --> 00:38:52,518
Thank you,

478
00:38:53,394 --> 00:38:54,228
Hui-seo.

479
00:38:56,564 --> 00:38:57,606
Sure.

480
00:38:57,690 --> 00:38:59,233
Don't forget to call Grandma.

481
00:38:59,316 --> 00:39:00,901
I'll call first thing in the morning.

482
00:39:01,986 --> 00:39:02,820
Okay, bye.

483
00:39:30,598 --> 00:39:33,601
This is for 2023.

484
00:39:40,900 --> 00:39:44,445
This is for 2022.

485
00:39:51,994 --> 00:39:54,497
This is for 2021.

486
00:40:23,901 --> 00:40:25,736
This godeulppaegi kimchi is amazing.

487
00:40:28,072 --> 00:40:29,281
Have it with some soup.

488
00:40:30,157 --> 00:40:32,159
I made a lot of kimchi.

489
00:40:32,868 --> 00:40:36,330
Who knows what might happen
when I visit the hospital next week?

490
00:40:36,413 --> 00:40:39,542
You're just going in for a checkup
and coming straight home.

491
00:40:40,584 --> 00:40:42,711
Tae-seo likes kimchi,

492
00:40:42,795 --> 00:40:44,880
but there's no way to get it to him.

493
00:40:58,060 --> 00:40:59,478
Why is there so much?

494
00:40:59,562 --> 00:41:02,356
It's a year's worth.
Some of it's for other clients too.

495
00:41:02,439 --> 00:41:03,649
Will Tae-seo be home?

496
00:41:03,732 --> 00:41:06,944
Of course not.
I can't fit into his schedule.

497
00:41:07,736 --> 00:41:10,406
I can just leave these inside.
It seems he got more jobs.

498
00:41:10,489 --> 00:41:12,324
-Jobs?
-Yeah.

499
00:41:13,492 --> 00:41:15,160
What on earth is he up to?

500
00:41:16,745 --> 00:41:17,746
I'm coming with you.

501
00:41:18,497 --> 00:41:21,333
I'll be coming back late at night
after I visit all my clients.

502
00:41:21,417 --> 00:41:23,210
That's fine by me.

503
00:41:24,044 --> 00:41:26,088
My brother will be shocked to see me.

504
00:41:26,171 --> 00:41:28,257
Are you sure you can go?
What about the post office?

505
00:41:29,008 --> 00:41:30,551
I worked the morning shift today.

506
00:41:31,594 --> 00:41:33,887
Are you here to pick up the wood?

507
00:41:33,971 --> 00:41:35,139
Don't tell my grandma.

508
00:41:35,222 --> 00:41:36,307
I'll say I'm going to work.

509
00:41:37,016 --> 00:41:38,267
Grandma.

510
00:41:38,350 --> 00:41:40,477
Jin-su said he can bring
the kimchi to Tae-seo.

511
00:41:40,561 --> 00:41:41,520
Could you pack some up?

512
00:41:42,354 --> 00:41:43,439
Goodness.

513
00:41:43,522 --> 00:41:46,233
Thank you so much.
I'll go pack it up right now, okay?

514
00:41:46,317 --> 00:41:47,443
Sure.

515
00:42:16,347 --> 00:42:17,598
"Amy Park."

516
00:42:56,637 --> 00:42:57,471
Amy Park.

517
00:42:58,347 --> 00:42:59,932
I came to see you.

518
00:43:10,025 --> 00:43:11,276
This is nice.

519
00:43:12,236 --> 00:43:13,862
I can't believe how nice it is.

520
00:43:15,155 --> 00:43:16,448
Have a pleasant stay.

521
00:43:21,870 --> 00:43:23,205
Eun-a.

522
00:43:24,373 --> 00:43:25,457
Mo Eun-a!

523
00:43:30,921 --> 00:43:32,131
Here, give it to me.

524
00:43:38,679 --> 00:43:41,265
Geez, I knew he'd be living like this.

525
00:43:41,849 --> 00:43:43,434
Cup noodles and rice snacks.

526
00:43:44,393 --> 00:43:45,352
Honestly.

527
00:43:50,023 --> 00:43:52,192
You're beaming
now that you're at your brother's.

528
00:43:52,943 --> 00:43:54,069
He'll be happy to see you.

529
00:43:55,988 --> 00:43:57,656
-You should go do your rounds.
-Okay.

530
00:43:57,740 --> 00:44:00,409
I'll call you on my way here.
I'll come as soon as possible.

531
00:44:01,201 --> 00:44:02,327
Don't worry about me.

532
00:44:02,411 --> 00:44:04,997
This is my brother's place.
I can sleep over if I have to.

533
00:44:09,460 --> 00:44:11,545
-See you.
-Bye.

534
00:44:14,214 --> 00:44:16,216
Geez, look at all that laundry
lying around.

535
00:44:17,593 --> 00:44:18,761
One, two.

536
00:44:20,888 --> 00:44:23,766
He still wears his gym shorts?
Are they his favorite or something?

537
00:44:44,369 --> 00:44:46,163
Of course, he's not here.

538
00:44:50,793 --> 00:44:53,337
I sent the painting by courier.

539
00:44:53,420 --> 00:44:56,381
He complained there was no elevator.

540
00:44:57,007 --> 00:44:58,759
-He left it in front of…
-Excuse me?

541
00:45:05,724 --> 00:45:06,683
Granny.

542
00:45:07,267 --> 00:45:10,354
It looks like Mo Eun-a's house
got international mail again.

543
00:45:11,063 --> 00:45:12,689
It's from Hawaii this time.

544
00:45:14,066 --> 00:45:15,234
Granny?

545
00:45:18,278 --> 00:45:19,154
Granny!

546
00:45:31,416 --> 00:45:32,834
You're Mr. Yeon Tae-seo's brother?

547
00:45:33,835 --> 00:45:35,462
Yes, why do you ask?

548
00:45:37,047 --> 00:45:38,799
I told him I'd send it by courier,

549
00:45:38,882 --> 00:45:40,801
but I had time so I came in person.

550
00:45:41,552 --> 00:45:43,011
You can just leave it here.

551
00:45:43,095 --> 00:45:43,929
Okay.

552
00:45:44,721 --> 00:45:46,223
I'll leave it with you.

553
00:45:52,980 --> 00:45:55,482
Hi, Hyang-gi. What is it?

554
00:46:06,410 --> 00:46:07,661
Could you help me up?

555
00:46:08,662 --> 00:46:09,621
Right, sure.

556
00:46:22,801 --> 00:46:24,970
3 MISSED CALLS

557
00:46:25,053 --> 00:46:26,346
OLD HOUSE IM A-SOL

558
00:46:31,810 --> 00:46:33,645
-I can't get into it right now.
-Sorry?

559
00:46:33,729 --> 00:46:35,689
Your grandmother collapsed.

560
00:46:35,772 --> 00:46:37,691
I met your brother at your house.

561
00:46:37,774 --> 00:46:40,319
We're on our way to the hospital,
so please come right away.

562
00:46:41,236 --> 00:46:42,529
I'll explain everything later.

563
00:46:42,613 --> 00:46:44,489
I was told you know which hospital it is.

564
00:46:44,573 --> 00:46:45,991
Please put Hui-seo on the phone.

565
00:46:49,995 --> 00:46:51,622
He's asleep. I think it was the nerves.

566
00:46:52,289 --> 00:46:54,249
He's allowed to visit his brother, right?

567
00:46:56,209 --> 00:46:58,629
As for me, I was going to send
the painting by courier, but--

568
00:46:58,712 --> 00:47:00,213
Hui-seo.

569
00:47:00,297 --> 00:47:01,632
You can hear me, right?

570
00:47:01,715 --> 00:47:04,426
I just finished my work,
so I can come right away.

571
00:47:05,135 --> 00:47:07,804
Don't get anxious
and massage your leg on the way.

572
00:47:08,555 --> 00:47:10,057
Don't be nervous. Keep breathing.

573
00:47:11,391 --> 00:47:12,309
It's okay.

574
00:47:13,602 --> 00:47:14,561
Okay, Tae-seo.

575
00:47:22,319 --> 00:47:25,906
Hello? I don't think
I can make tomorrow's shift.

576
00:47:26,573 --> 00:47:28,659
Yes. Okay, thank you.

577
00:47:34,539 --> 00:47:36,625
Let's get some bean sprout and rice soup.

578
00:47:36,708 --> 00:47:39,461
I'm feeling a bit sick
after all that wine on the plane.

579
00:47:39,544 --> 00:47:40,629
I need to cure my hangover.

580
00:47:42,214 --> 00:47:44,007
I'll have one delivered here, ma'am.

581
00:47:44,091 --> 00:47:47,135
Let's go to a restaurant and eat!

582
00:47:53,266 --> 00:47:54,935
That hits the spot.

583
00:47:56,019 --> 00:47:57,479
I feel so much better now.

584
00:48:00,774 --> 00:48:03,110
It's a good thing
you broke up with Seong-chan.

585
00:48:03,193 --> 00:48:06,571
He has to have you all to himself
and make you work with only him,

586
00:48:06,655 --> 00:48:07,656
so you end up all alone.

587
00:48:08,240 --> 00:48:10,033
So you still talk to him.

588
00:48:10,117 --> 00:48:11,284
But he's not a bad person.

589
00:48:12,119 --> 00:48:13,370
He's paying for the lawsuit.

590
00:48:14,579 --> 00:48:16,581
He doesn't even have that kind of money.

591
00:48:16,665 --> 00:48:18,917
He's going to spend
his entire life savings on that suit.

592
00:48:19,668 --> 00:48:21,503
That's not going to solve anything.

593
00:48:24,756 --> 00:48:25,799
I'm not done yet.

594
00:48:26,425 --> 00:48:27,801
Don't stay at Na-yeong's either.

595
00:48:27,884 --> 00:48:30,303
Why are you wandering around
as if you don't have a home?

596
00:48:30,387 --> 00:48:32,180
When Na-yeong told me where you worked,

597
00:48:32,264 --> 00:48:34,057
she acted like
she was doing me a huge favor.

598
00:48:34,141 --> 00:48:37,644
There's only one person
who knows where I am and told Na-yeong.

599
00:48:38,937 --> 00:48:40,063
Now, to the main point.

600
00:48:41,440 --> 00:48:42,691
The guesthouse you used to run.

601
00:48:43,400 --> 00:48:44,443
You need to go back to it.

602
00:48:48,530 --> 00:48:52,159
Seong-chan's bent on a lawsuit
I didn't even ask for, and now you.

603
00:48:52,826 --> 00:48:55,203
What's with you two? What is your deal?

604
00:48:55,287 --> 00:48:56,997
I don't know what he's thinking.

605
00:48:57,914 --> 00:48:59,583
I came to settle your situation.

606
00:49:00,751 --> 00:49:02,002
That guesthouse you ran.

607
00:49:02,085 --> 00:49:04,254
Seong-chan only found out
about it through me.

608
00:49:08,717 --> 00:49:10,552
How else would he have known?

609
00:49:11,428 --> 00:49:14,806
I knew about it because
I was going around looking into things.

610
00:49:17,100 --> 00:49:20,520
I'm saying the property owner
is someone I know.

611
00:49:21,688 --> 00:49:22,981
I'm going to settle this.

612
00:49:24,357 --> 00:49:27,819
You just take back what's yours
and go back to living your life.

613
00:49:30,071 --> 00:49:31,531
You're at it again.

614
00:49:32,115 --> 00:49:33,658
Are you that desperate to play my mom?

615
00:49:33,742 --> 00:49:36,495
You should be good to your own mother
and stop causing her grief.

616
00:49:40,248 --> 00:49:42,209
I'm here because my mom made such a fuss.

617
00:49:43,293 --> 00:49:45,754
She prays for you at dawn every day.

618
00:49:45,837 --> 00:49:48,381
She barely knows you,
and yet she prefers you over me.

619
00:49:54,721 --> 00:49:57,849
You have the right to stay there
until your lease is up,

620
00:49:57,933 --> 00:49:58,892
so run your guesthouse.

621
00:49:59,851 --> 00:50:01,561
After that, I can't stop them.

622
00:50:02,229 --> 00:50:03,230
Then…

623
00:50:07,567 --> 00:50:08,735
go back to Yeonwoo.

624
00:50:10,737 --> 00:50:11,780
It's your home.

625
00:50:14,574 --> 00:50:17,536
-If you don't like Yeonwoo…
-You go to Yeonwoo.

626
00:50:19,204 --> 00:50:20,831
It's been empty for ten years.

627
00:50:27,712 --> 00:50:29,631
Anything else you want me to do?

628
00:50:30,215 --> 00:50:31,883
Anything while I'm there?

629
00:50:34,594 --> 00:50:35,637
You're not going to do

630
00:50:37,430 --> 00:50:39,015
what I ask you to do anyway.

631
00:50:42,310 --> 00:50:44,855
I asked you to stay by his side.

632
00:50:48,358 --> 00:50:49,734
I have a lot to say too.

633
00:50:52,195 --> 00:50:53,363
This grief

634
00:50:54,155 --> 00:50:55,949
can only be shared

635
00:50:57,659 --> 00:50:59,661
by you and me.

636
00:51:01,371 --> 00:51:02,581
In this world…

637
00:51:04,499 --> 00:51:05,792
there's no one else.

638
00:51:07,335 --> 00:51:08,879
We should at least

639
00:51:10,338 --> 00:51:11,590
look out for each other

640
00:51:12,757 --> 00:51:14,551
and be honest about how we feel.

641
00:51:22,142 --> 00:51:23,184
Let's stay together today.

642
00:51:24,019 --> 00:51:25,228
At least for today.

643
00:51:25,854 --> 00:51:28,356
I won't be able to sleep
from the jet lag anyway,

644
00:51:28,440 --> 00:51:29,691
so let's catch up…

645
00:51:37,282 --> 00:51:39,409
This is exactly why I didn't want to come.

646
00:52:01,973 --> 00:52:02,974
I'm on my way to Yeonwoo.

647
00:52:03,808 --> 00:52:05,310
My grandma suddenly collapsed.

648
00:52:05,894 --> 00:52:08,772
Hui-seo's not doing so well either,
so I'm going to stay with him.

649
00:52:12,192 --> 00:52:13,360
Is she okay?

650
00:52:18,949 --> 00:52:19,783
She has to be.

651
00:52:22,619 --> 00:52:23,662
This grief

652
00:52:24,245 --> 00:52:25,789
can only be shared

653
00:52:25,872 --> 00:52:27,958
by you and me.

654
00:52:29,584 --> 00:52:30,752
Let's stay together today.

655
00:52:31,670 --> 00:52:32,921
At least for today.

656
00:52:59,698 --> 00:53:00,949
Eun-a, is that you?

657
00:53:22,637 --> 00:53:23,471
Hello.

658
00:53:24,889 --> 00:53:27,642
First off, we've taken care
of the bleeding.

659
00:53:27,726 --> 00:53:29,144
Given the patient's age,

660
00:53:29,227 --> 00:53:31,312
recovery may take a bit longer.

661
00:53:31,396 --> 00:53:33,231
But the surgery went well,

662
00:53:33,314 --> 00:53:35,066
so let's see how it goes.

663
00:53:35,817 --> 00:53:37,569
-All right, then.
-Thank you.

664
00:54:07,807 --> 00:54:08,641
Basically…

665
00:54:09,517 --> 00:54:13,104
Grandma wanted to send you
some of her godeulppaegi kimchi,

666
00:54:14,564 --> 00:54:17,067
and I wanted to lift her spirits
before the checkup.

667
00:54:17,150 --> 00:54:18,818
That's why I went…

668
00:54:19,986 --> 00:54:21,071
Good.

669
00:54:21,654 --> 00:54:23,656
It's about time you got out of Yeonwoo.

670
00:54:29,079 --> 00:54:31,664
It's purely psychological,
so be confident in yourself.

671
00:54:31,748 --> 00:54:34,793
You have strength in your leg,
so you'll be discharged in a week.

672
00:54:34,876 --> 00:54:36,169
You're perfectly healthy.

673
00:54:38,088 --> 00:54:39,380
It's swollen.

674
00:54:41,341 --> 00:54:43,384
Don't tell Grandma.

675
00:54:43,468 --> 00:54:45,220
It won't help with her recovery.

676
00:54:49,641 --> 00:54:51,184
And do that girl's frame for free.

677
00:54:51,935 --> 00:54:53,311
The girl who drove me here.

678
00:54:54,145 --> 00:54:55,355
I will.

679
00:55:05,156 --> 00:55:07,325
I had some extra soft tofu stew
at a famous spot,

680
00:55:07,408 --> 00:55:08,535
and I'm about to depart now.

681
00:55:09,202 --> 00:55:10,370
How did the surgery go?

682
00:55:11,412 --> 00:55:12,539
It went well.

683
00:55:13,373 --> 00:55:14,415
What a relief.

684
00:55:15,333 --> 00:55:18,461
I kept imagining the worst,
so I couldn't even eat properly.

685
00:55:19,671 --> 00:55:20,839
Where are you right now?

686
00:55:43,695 --> 00:55:44,737
Grandpa.

687
00:55:45,947 --> 00:55:46,781
Hey.

688
00:55:51,578 --> 00:55:55,248
The person who drove Hui-seo here
is still in Gangneung.

689
00:55:55,999 --> 00:55:58,710
She's heading to Seoul now,
so I'm going to drive her back.

690
00:55:59,919 --> 00:56:01,754
Yeah, you should.

691
00:56:02,839 --> 00:56:04,382
Don't worry about things here.

692
00:56:08,178 --> 00:56:12,724
The surgery went well, so she'll be fine.

693
00:56:16,227 --> 00:56:18,146
I'll come right back tomorrow morning.

694
00:56:20,023 --> 00:56:21,774
Just rest at home.

695
00:56:21,858 --> 00:56:23,902
You'll be driving all night.

696
00:56:27,864 --> 00:56:29,115
No, I'll come.

697
00:56:41,669 --> 00:56:44,505
TAE-SEO, I'LL WAIT FOR YOU
KEEP ME UPDATED EVEN IF IT'S LATE

698
00:56:46,591 --> 00:56:51,346
I was wondering whether I should
stay the night and leave tomorrow.

699
00:56:53,097 --> 00:56:57,185
If you get short-term car insurance,
I can drive your car.

700
00:56:57,977 --> 00:57:00,605
Add me as the driver. I'll pay the fee.

701
00:57:02,482 --> 00:57:03,358
That's a thing?

702
00:57:08,154 --> 00:57:09,781
ONE-DAY CAR INSURANCE

703
00:57:09,864 --> 00:57:11,032
I found it.

704
00:57:11,699 --> 00:57:12,617
I'd be very grateful.

705
00:57:13,826 --> 00:57:15,286
I'm the one who's grateful.

706
00:57:16,537 --> 00:57:18,623
Hui-seo never really comes to my place.

707
00:57:21,167 --> 00:57:23,169
So that's where you live. Your place.

708
00:57:25,338 --> 00:57:28,049
It kicks in at midnight, so…

709
00:57:29,968 --> 00:57:31,511
Can we stay for ten more minutes?

710
00:57:32,845 --> 00:57:33,680
Sure.

711
00:57:43,606 --> 00:57:45,108
The surgery went well.

712
00:57:45,191 --> 00:57:46,401
You don't need to worry.

713
00:57:47,819 --> 00:57:49,445
I knew it would.

714
00:57:49,529 --> 00:57:50,905
I know your grandma well.

715
00:57:51,614 --> 00:57:52,991
She's strong.

716
00:58:00,498 --> 00:58:01,749
-Hey, Hyeong-seok.
-Hey!

717
00:58:02,458 --> 00:58:03,960
Was the name tag…

718
00:58:04,043 --> 00:58:05,378
Was it Im Ji-sol?

719
00:58:05,461 --> 00:58:08,506
If it was, you can't do that to me.

720
00:58:08,590 --> 00:58:10,800
You should've told me.

721
00:58:10,883 --> 00:58:11,718
It wasn't.

722
00:58:11,801 --> 00:58:15,221
I asked her out
and got completely humiliated.

723
00:58:15,305 --> 00:58:16,764
When I think about that time…

724
00:58:20,018 --> 00:58:21,686
It still makes me cringe.

725
00:58:21,769 --> 00:58:24,063
I must've been out of my mind back then.

726
00:58:24,981 --> 00:58:26,524
Hey, hang up.

727
00:58:26,608 --> 00:58:28,901
I'm going to call Mi-ju.

728
00:58:28,985 --> 00:58:31,070
Yeah, you do that. Bye.

729
00:58:34,866 --> 00:58:36,117
Im Ji-sol?

730
00:58:37,952 --> 00:58:39,245
Im Ji-sol…

731
00:58:50,089 --> 00:58:51,007
Im A-sol.

732
00:59:04,896 --> 00:59:07,148
You can sleep the whole way there.

733
00:59:07,815 --> 00:59:09,525
You must be exhausted.

734
00:59:10,485 --> 00:59:13,196
It's a long night drive,
so I should keep you company.

735
00:59:14,781 --> 00:59:16,324
I'll drive to where you live.

736
00:59:16,407 --> 00:59:18,493
No, you can drive to yours.

737
00:59:18,576 --> 00:59:19,952
My place isn't far from there.

738
00:59:21,037 --> 00:59:24,499
It'll be dawn when we get to Seoul.
You won't be able to find a cab.

739
00:59:38,054 --> 00:59:40,056
-All right, let's go.
-Okay.

740
00:59:47,730 --> 00:59:49,023
By the way…

741
00:59:51,234 --> 00:59:52,360
Weren't you asleep?

742
00:59:52,443 --> 00:59:53,611
Earlier…

743
00:59:54,237 --> 00:59:56,280
you said you'd drive to where I live.

744
00:59:56,864 --> 00:59:58,533
How did you know?

745
00:59:59,283 --> 01:00:00,827
When we first met,

746
01:00:02,036 --> 01:00:04,539
you went home while we were talking
to get the painting.

747
01:00:05,915 --> 01:00:07,959
You said it was five minutes
from where we met.

748
01:00:08,042 --> 01:00:09,335
Right.

749
01:00:09,419 --> 01:00:13,631
And you're the only person who's allowed
takeout at the restaurant with my frame.

750
01:00:14,257 --> 01:00:16,551
And you studied
at Hyeong-seok's study center.

751
01:00:25,226 --> 01:00:27,186
My name tag's in Yeonwoo, isn't it?

752
01:00:28,938 --> 01:00:31,315
No wonder I felt drawn to that place.

753
01:00:33,401 --> 01:00:35,361
Then, let's be friends from now on.

754
01:00:35,445 --> 01:00:36,863
You don't mind, right?

755
01:00:36,946 --> 01:00:37,989
Well…

756
01:00:38,072 --> 01:00:39,991
Okay, we've cleared that up.

757
01:00:40,074 --> 01:00:42,452
Anything you want to ask me
about the past?

758
01:00:42,535 --> 01:00:44,620
-You can go ahead.
-I don't.

759
01:00:46,956 --> 01:00:48,958
Go to sleep, Ms. Im. We'll be a while.

760
01:00:50,418 --> 01:00:51,711
I said we should be friends.

761
01:00:56,048 --> 01:00:56,924
Sleep.

762
01:01:16,778 --> 01:01:18,404
SEONG-CHAN

763
01:01:28,748 --> 01:01:31,042
You know how to get home from here, right?

764
01:01:47,141 --> 01:01:51,354
I came because I missed her,
but maybe I shouldn't have come.

765
01:01:51,437 --> 01:01:52,438
How's Eun-a?

766
01:01:54,774 --> 01:01:55,733
It's just upsetting

767
01:01:56,442 --> 01:02:00,196
to see her struggling alone
in an empty guesthouse.

768
01:03:23,487 --> 01:03:24,530
Get away from there.

769
01:03:50,222 --> 01:03:53,726
STILL SHINING

770
01:04:19,710 --> 01:04:22,088
You put so much care and effort
into that place.

771
01:04:22,171 --> 01:04:25,383
Now you can have it all back.
What exactly is the problem?

772
01:04:25,967 --> 01:04:29,929
Does that Seong-chan guy
have something to do with your guesthouse?

773
01:04:30,721 --> 01:04:32,264
I'm not in Seoul.

774
01:04:32,348 --> 01:04:34,600
Missing each other,
being drained emotionally…

775
01:04:34,684 --> 01:04:36,394
I'll explain everything in person.

776
01:04:36,477 --> 01:04:38,562
We were talking about our future
just the other day.

777
01:04:38,646 --> 01:04:40,898
I have to make it back today.

778
01:04:40,982 --> 01:04:42,566
In the past decade of Eun-a's life,

779
01:04:44,777 --> 01:04:45,987
he was the only one present.

780
01:04:52,535 --> 01:04:54,537
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee
